{
  "texts": [
    "During inference, the decoder predicts tokens in time steps, one token at a time.",
    "The decoder adds each predicted token to the input context window to build the input sequence and then predicts the next token based on the updated objective function.",
    "The looping terminates when the input receives a special stop token.",
    "The exploded view of the decoder in the middle of Fig. 16 shows that the output of the attention mechanism feeds into a residual connection, which then feeds into a layer normalization block that standardizes the batch of co-relevance vectors.",
    "The FFNN (FF n) at each token position independently adjusts the co-relevance vector at that position to further refine its meaning in preparation for more self-attention processing in later decoder layers."
  ]
}